(1, 1, 'processed', 'document', 'application/json', 'input', 0, 'generic', '{\n    "action": "add",\n    "locale_1": "fr-FR",\n    "type": "text\\/html",\n    "path": "\\/root\\/public\\/resources\\/",\n    "name": "deontology_chart",\n    "summary": "<h4 style=\\"text-align: left;\\">Why having choosen this project ?<\\/h4><blockquote>Why P-PIT ? As a mean to contribute to deliver the promise of technology. Since 30 years, I have been following the main IT evolutions: The desktop, the enterprise applications, the Internet thriving, the smartphone. Huge progresses in fact, but at the same time a more and more complex accumulation of solution parcels without a real consistency as a whole.<\\/blockquote>",\n    "summary_locale_1": "<h4 style=\\"text-align: left;\\">Pourquoi avoir entrepris ce projet ?<\\/h4><blockquote>Pourquoi P-PIT ? Pour contribuer \\u00e0 d\\u00e9livrer enfin la promesse du progr\\u00e8s technologique. Depuis 30 ans, j\\u2019ai suivi les grandes \\u00e9volutions de l\\u2019informatique : Le poste de travail, les applications d\\u2019entreprise, l\\u2019essor de l\\u2019internet, le smartphone. Des progr\\u00e8s consid\\u00e9rables certes, mais en parall\\u00e8le un empilement de plus en plus complexe d\\u2019\\u00eelots de solutions sans v\\u00e9ritable coh\\u00e9rence d\\u2019ensemble.<\\/blockquote>",\n    "properties": {\n        "title": "Deontology chart",\n        "description": "",\n        "date": "2017-05-07"\n    },\n    "properties_locale_1": {\n        "title": "Charte dÃ©ontologique",\n        "description": "",\n        "date": "2017-05-07"\n    },\n    "parts": [{\n        "content": "<div style=\\"font-size: 85%\\"><h4 style=\\"color: darkmagenta\\">CHARTE DEONTOLOGIQUE Version en date du 01/09/2016</h4><h5>1. PREAMBULE<\\/h5><p>This Chart aims at recalling to the User of the 2Pit free solution the main principles of international law applicable to the Internet, associated with a a short comment as an illustration. Though the attention given to the redaction of this appendix, The 2Pit community cannot assume whatever responsability about possibly lacking informations, the present chart being by no means to be considered as presenting any exhaustivity. Furthermore, it is up to the User to refer to the whole legal frame being relevant to his context.</p><p>So the 2Pit community strongly advises the User to ask for a consulting in order to address his specific problem. The User is responsible of the comments and content standing in his own site.</p><p>It is clarified, first, that the User manages at his own matters of any legal, regulatory or administrative authorizations necessary to the setting or running of the Internet site.</p><p>Secondly, the user commit t respect in the frame of the running of the site, the legal and deontological rules governing the exercice of its prodession, and more generally the expected use of ths Internet site.</p><p>In any event, the User is responsible of the respect of common decency and public order, of the respect of lawds and regulating, especially regarding child protection and espect of human being. He commit in the same conditions to respect of the rules concerning personal data protection and more generally to the rules concerning third-party rights, regarding in particular intellectual property rights, and rights relative to information and web sites content.</p><h5>2. COMMUNICATION SERVICES FOR THE ONLINE PUBLIC</h5><p>A distinction is made between different people able to act on a web site</p><h6>2.1 â The Internet access provider</h6><p>He is defined as the person whose activity is to offer an access to communication services for the online public.</p><p>He is responsible to inform his subscribers on the existence of technical means allowing to restrict the access to or select certain services and to propose them at least one of these means.</p><p>He is also responsible to infom them on the existence of means to securize their network.</p><h6>2.2 â The host</h6><p>He is defined as the physic or moral person who ensure, even for free, as to provide the public by the mean of the communication services for the online public, the storage of signals, documents, images, sounds and messages of any nature supplied by offerees of these services.</p><p>The host should not be mistaken for the service provider who, as the case may be, let for the benefit of the host a dedicated service, such a service provider just providing a technical infrastructure.</p><h6>2.3 â The publisher of a communication service for the online public.</h6><p>The publisher of the site will provide the public, in an open standard, with:</p><ul><li>in the case of a public person: his last name, first name, place of residence ans phone number, along with if necessary the registration number on legal files,</li><li>in the case of a moral person: his denomination, his head office, phone numbers, registration number in legal files, share capital, name of the director of publication, the name, address and phone number of his host.</li></ul><p>The publisher will also take care to display:</p><ul><li>the applicable fare as the case may be,</li><li>the advertising character of the webcasted messages.</li></ul><p>However, in the case of a sited published as non-professional, the publisher, in order to preserve his anonymity, is allowed to just provide the public, with only the name and address of his host, while taking care of beforehand insure he has communicated to the last, his personal identification informations.</p><p>The constatation of an illicit content should give rise to a request formulated directly to the site publisher. In case of absence of the last, and since the content present an obviously illicit character, a dated notification can be addressed to the host with mention of the name and address of the addressee, the description of the litigious facts and their precise localization, the motivation for having the content retired, including the mention of legal dispositions and fact justifications, along with the copy of the correspondence addressed to the author or publisher of the litigious content, asking for its removal, its modification or, failing this, the justification of the author or publisher not being possibly reachable.</p><p>The host has, in this respect, no general obligation of supervision of the contents he hosts.</p><p>Finally, there exists rules which apply to all the service providers as information medium which are related, for the most, to the public order protection and the public decency respect.</p><h5>3. PUBLIC ORDER</h5><p>Nobody can depart from laws relative to public order.</p><p>The confusion in public order is an evident breach of the public peace.</p><h5>4. Public decency and youth</h5><p>Nobody can depart from laws relative to public decency.</p><p>Affront to public decency is defined by the fact either to make, transport, spread by whatever mean and with whatever support a message with a violent or pornographic character or with a nature which could seriously strike a blow at human dignity or encourage minor people to give oneself up to games physically putting them in danger, either to make business of such a message.</p><h5>5. INCENTIVE TO SUICIDE</h5><p>Are especially targeted:</p><ul><li>the fact of provoke suicide, while the provocation has been followed by a suicide or a suicide attempt. As such, one could considere the Internet as a vector of provocation;</li><li>the propaganda or advertising, whatever the mean, in favor of products, objects or methods advocated as means to give oneself death;</li><li>the fact, by the mean of whatever process, to voluntarily strike a blow at others private lifeâs intimity.</li></ul><h5>6. PROCURING</h5><p>Is targeted the fact by anyone, whatever the mean:</p><ul><li>To help, assist or protect others prostitution;</li><li>To benefit from others prostitution, to share the products of it or to receive the subsidies from a person regularily engaged to prostitution;</li><li>To hire, train, or divert a person towards prostitution or to pu pressure on her in order to prostitute or go on prostituting.</li></ul><p>It is worth remarking that can be assimilated to procuring the fact, by whoever, whith whatever mean, to act as an intermediary between two persons, one of whom is engaged to prostitution, and the other exploits or remunerates others prostitution.</p><h5>7. BREACH TO AUTOMATED DATA PROCESSING SYSTEMS</h5><p>Are specifically targeted:</p><ul><li>the fact of accessing or staying fraudulently inside the whole or a part of an automated data processing system;</li><li>the fact of hindering or skewing the functioning of such a system;</li><li>the fact of introducing fraudulently data in such a system or suppressing or or fradulently modifying the contained data.</li></ul><h5>8. MISLEADING ADVERTISING - CONSUMER PROTECTION</h5><p>The provider of a web site should make sure that the messages being webcasted do not consist of false elements or likely to lead one abstray.</p><p>For any distance sale offer for a good or a service which is made to a consumer, the professional will mention the name of his enterprise, his phone number, the address of his head office and, if different, the one of theplace responsible of the offer, along with the name of the person considered as the publication responsible.</p><h5>9. LEGAL DISPOSITIONS RELATIVE TO NARCOTIC SUBSTANCES</h5><p>According to local laws, can be liable to imprisonment and fines:</p><ul><li>The provocation to illicit use of stupefiants or to stupefiant traffic, even if that provocation has no been followed by any effect, or the fact to present favorably these offences;</li><li>The provocation, even if not followed by effects, to the use of substances presented as having the effects of substances or plants that are classed as stupefiants;</li><li>The transportation, detention, offer, transfer, purchase or illicit use of stupefiants;</li><li>the fact of facilitating, by whatever mean, the illicit use of stupefiants, of obtaining stupefiants by the mean of fictifious prescription, or of delivering stupefiants based on the presentation of such prescriptions, while knowing the fictifious character;</li><li>the provocation of a minor person to using stupefiants;</li><li>the provocation of a minor person to the stupefiant traffic;</li><li>the illicit production or making of stupefiants;</li><li>the illicit import or export of stupefiants.</li></ul><h5>10. INFORMATIONS</h5><h6>10.1 Informations authentication</h6><p>The information origin should be clearly mentioned, and concerning a comment, the author should be designed by name.</p><h6>10.2.False informations</h6><p>The fact of communicating or leaking a false information in order to persuade that a destruction, a degradation or a dangerous degradation for persons is about to be, or has been committed, ot of communicating or leaking a false information in order to persuade about a disaster, and to cause the unnecessary intervention of first aid is punishable.</p><h5>11. DISCRIMINATION</h5><p>Constitute a discrimination, any distinction made between physical persons for the reason of their origin, sex, family situation, state of wealth, handicap, manners, political opinions, union activity, belonging or non-belonging, real or supposed, to an ethnic group, a nation, a race or a particular religion.</p><p>Also constitue a discrimination any distinction made between moral persons for the reason of the origin, sex, family situation, state of wealth, handicap, manners, political opinions, union activity, belonging or non-belonging, real or supposed, to an ethnic group, a nation, a race or a particular religion of members or some of te members of these moral persons.</p><p>The discrimination towards a physical or a moral person is punishable each time it consists in particular to refuse the providing of a good or service at a condition founded on one of the elements targeted before.</p><h5>12. INFRINGEMENT TO THE PERSON REPRESENTATION</h5><p>The fact of publishing, by whatever medium, the editing realized with the speech or the image of a person without his or her consent, each time it does not appears clearly that it is an editing, or if it is not expressly mentioned is punishable..</p><h5>13. PROTECTION OF THE PERSON</h5><p>The fact of volontarily undermining, by whatever process, to someone privacy is punishable.</p><h5>14. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY AND UNFAIR COMPETITION</h5><p>The intellectual property regulation prohibit any reuse of a work of the mind without the author consent. Likewise, any illicit use of marks constitutes an infringement, including in the metatags of Internet sites.</p><p>Furthermore, software and the underlying technology linked to sites are protected and can only be reused with the express consent of the holder of the rights.</p><p>Independently of the acts subject to constitute an counterfeit, ny reuse of rights belonging to others could be sued as regards to unfair competition, and lead to the implication of the offenderâs responsability.</p><p>In particular, before inserting a deep link towards a third-party site, it is recommanded to verify is such a link is licit, or to ask the authorization of the target site, in order to prevent from any act which could reveal a posteriori as constituting an unfair competition.</p><h5>15. PERSONAL DATA</h5><p>Any physic or moral person engaged in the collect of personal data, freely or for a fee, is bound to proceed to an ad hoc declaration of the process of automation of the collect of these data.</p><p>For example, is considered as being a personal data a simple email address which collect should consequently be declared.</p><p>It will also be necessary to inform the persons whose data are collected about the finality of the implemented processes, about the possibility of rectification and, if necessary, of opposition to the data that concerns them.</p><h5>16. HEALTH PERSONAL DATA</h5><p>The persons who practise the activity of hosting health personal data should own an agreement conforming to legal prescriptions.</p><p>2Pit recalls to the user that it is his/her responsability to refer to the list of authorized hosts for any health personal data hosting.</p>",\n        "content_locale_1": "<div style=\\"font-size: 85%\\"><h4 style=\\"color: darkmagenta\\">CHARTE DEONTOLOGIQUE Version en date du 01/09/2016</h4><h5>1. PREAMBULE</h5><p>La prÃ©sente Charte a pour objet de rappeler Ã  lâUtilisateur de la solution libre 2Pit les principales rÃ¨gles de droit international applicables Ã  lâInternet, associÃ©s Ã  un court commentaire Ã  titre dâillustration. MalgrÃ© lâattention portÃ©e Ã  la rÃ©daction de cette annexe, la communautÃ© 2Pit ne peut assumer une quelconque responsabilitÃ© du fait des informations qui nây sont pas contenues, la prÃ©sente charte ne pouvant en aucun cas Ãªtre considÃ©rÃ©e comme prÃ©sentant un caractÃ¨re exhaustif. Par ailleurs, il appartient Ã  lâUtilisateur de se reporter Ã  lâensemble du cadre lÃ©gal le concernant.</p><p>La communautÃ© 2Pit conseille donc fortement Ã  lâUtilisateur de sâadresser Ã  un conseil pour traiter de son problÃ¨me particulier. Lâutilisateur est responsable des propos et des contenus figurant sur son propre site.</p><p>Il est prÃ©cisÃ©, en premier lieu, que lâUtilisateur fait son affaire personnelle de toutes les autorisations lÃ©gales, rÃ©glementaires ou administratives nÃ©cessaires Ã  lâouverture et Ã  lâexploitation du site Internet.</p><p>En second lieu, lâutilisateur sâengage Ã  respecter dans le cadre de lâexploitation du site, les rÃ¨gles lÃ©gales et dÃ©ontologiques pouvant rÃ©gir lâexercice de sa profession, et plus gÃ©nÃ©ralement lâutilisation quâil envisage du site Internet.</p><p>En tout Ã©tat de cause, lâUtilisateur est responsable du respect des bonnes mÅurs et de lâordre public, du respect des Lois et RÃ¨glements, notamment en matiÃ¨re de protection des mineurs et du respect de la personne humaine. Il sâengage dans les mÃªmes conditions au respect des rÃ¨gles relatives Ã  la protection des donnÃ©es Ã  caractÃ¨re personnel et plus gÃ©nÃ©ralement de celles relatives aux droits des tiers, en particulier concernant les droits de propriÃ©tÃ© intellectuelle, ainsi que les droits relatifs Ã  lâinformation et au contenu des sites web.</p><h5>2. SERVICES DE COMMUNICATION AU PUBLIC EN LIGNE</h5><p>Une distinction est faite entre les diffÃ©rentes personnes susceptibles dâintervenir sur un site Internet</p><h6>2.1 â Le fournisseur dâaccÃ¨s Ã  Internet</h6><p>Il est dÃ©fini comme la personne dont lâactivitÃ© est dâoffrir un accÃ¨s Ã  des services de communication au public en ligne.</p><p>Il lui appartient dâinformer ses abonnÃ©s de lâexistence de moyens techniques permettant de restreindre lâaccÃ¨s Ã  certains services ou de les sÃ©lectionner et de leur proposer au moins un de ces moyens.</p><p>Il lui appartient Ã©galement de les informer de lâexistence de moyens de sÃ©curisation de leur rÃ©seau.</p><h6>2.2 â LâhÃ©bergeur</h6><p>Il est dÃ©fini comme la personne physique ou morale qui assure, mÃªme Ã  titre gratuit, pour mise Ã  disposition du public par les services de communication au public en ligne, le stockage de signaux, dâÃ©crits, dâimages, de sons ou de messages de toute nature fournis par des destinataires de ces services.</p><p>LâhÃ©bergeur ne doit pas Ãªtre confondu avec le prestataire qui, le cas Ã©chÃ©ant, loue au profit de lâhÃ©bergeur un serveur dÃ©diÃ©, un tel prestataire se contentant de mettre Ã  disposition une infrastructure technique.</p><h6>2.3 â LâÃ©diteur dâun service de communication au public en ligne.</h6><p>LâÃ©diteur du site mettra Ã  disposition du public, dans un standard ouvert :</p><ul><li>sâil sâagit dâune personne physique : ses nom, prÃ©nom, domicile et numÃ©ros de tÃ©lÃ©phone, ainsi que le cas Ã©chÃ©ant le numÃ©ro de son inscription dans les registres lÃ©gaux,</li><li>sâil sâagit dâune personne morale : sa dÃ©nomination, son siÃ¨ge social, numÃ©ros de tÃ©lÃ©phone, numÃ©ro de son inscription dans les registres lÃ©gaux, capital social, le nom du directeur de la publication, le nom, lâadresse et les numÃ©ros de tÃ©lÃ©phone de son hÃ©bergeur.</li></ul><p>LâÃ©diteur veillera Ã©galement Ã  afficher :</p><ul><li>le tarif applicable le cas Ã©chÃ©ant,</li><li>le caractÃ¨re publicitaire des messages diffusÃ©s.</li></ul><p>Toutefois, lorsque le site est Ã©ditÃ© Ã  titre non professionnel, lâÃ©diteur, afin de prÃ©server son anonymat, peut se contenter de tenir Ã  la disposition du public, uniquement le nom et lâadresse de son hÃ©bergeur, en ayant pris le soin de sâassurer quâil a prÃ©alablement communiquÃ© Ã  ce dernier, ses Ã©lÃ©ments dâidentification personnelle.</p><p>La constatation dâun contenu illicite doit donner lieu Ã  une demande formulÃ©e directement auprÃ¨s de lâÃ©diteur du site. En cas de carence de ce dernier, et dÃ¨s lors que le contenu prÃ©sente un caractÃ¨re manifestement illicite, une notification datÃ©e pourra Ãªtre adressÃ©e Ã  lâhÃ©bergeur en indiquant les coordonnÃ©es du notifiant, les nom et adresse du destinataire, la description des faits litigieux et leur localisation prÃ©cise, les motifs pour lesquels le contenu doit Ãªtre retirÃ©, comprenant la mention des dispositions lÃ©gales et des justifications de fait, ainsi que la copie de la correspondance adressÃ©e Ã  lâauteur ou Ã  lâÃ©diteur du contenu litigieux, demandant son retrait, sa modification ou, Ã  dÃ©faut, la justification de ce que lâauteur ou lâÃ©diteur nâa pu Ãªtre contactÃ©.</p><p>LâhÃ©bergeur nâa, Ã  cet Ã©gard, aucune obligation gÃ©nÃ©rale de surveillance des contenus quâil hÃ©berge.</p><p>Enfin, il existe des rÃ¨gles qui sâappliquent Ã  tous les fournisseurs de service en tant que supports dâinformation et qui ont trait, pour la plupart, Ã  la protection de lâordre public et au respect des bonnes mÅurs.</p><h5>3. ORDRE PUBLIC</h5><p>Nul ne peut dÃ©roger aux lois qui intÃ©ressent lâordre public.</p><p>Le trouble Ã  lâordre public est une atteinte manifeste Ã  la paix publique.</p><h5>4. BONNES MOEURS ET JEUNESSE</h5><p>Nul ne peut dÃ©roger aux lois qui intÃ©ressent les bonnes mÅurs.</p><p>Lâoutrage aux bonnes mÅurs est dÃ©fini par le fait soit de fabriquer, de transporter, de diffuser par quelque moyen que ce soit et quel quâen soit le support un message Ã  caractÃ¨re violent ou pornographique ou de nature Ã  porter gravement atteinte Ã  la dignitÃ© humaine ou Ã  inciter des mineurs Ã  se livrer Ã  des jeux les mettant physiquement en danger, soit de faire commerce dâun tel message.</p><h5>5. INCITATION AU SUICIDE</h5><p>Sont visÃ©s notamment :</p><ul><li>Le fait de provoquer au suicide, lorsque la provocation a Ã©tÃ© suivie dâun suicide ou dâune tentative de suicide. A ce titre, on pourrait considÃ©rer comme vecteur de provocation lâInternet ;</li><li>La propagande ou la publicitÃ©, quel quâen soit le mode, en faveur de produits, objets ou de mÃ©thodes prÃ©conisÃ©s comme moyens de se donner la mort;</li><li>Le fait, au moyen dâun procÃ©dÃ© quelconque, de porter volontairement atteinte Ã  lâintimitÃ© de la vie privÃ©e dâautrui.</li></ul><h5>6. PROXENETISME</h5><p>Sont visÃ©s le fait par quiconque, de quelque maniÃ¨re que ce soit :</p><ul><li>Dâaider, dâassister ou de protÃ©ger la prostitution dâautrui ;</li><li>De tirer profit de la prostitution dâautrui, dâen partager les produits ou de recevoir les subsides dâune personne se livrant habituellement Ã  la prostitution ;</li><li>Dâembaucher, dâentraÃ®ner ou de dÃ©tourner une personne en vue de la prostitution ou dâexercer sur elle une pression pour quâelle se prostitue ou continue Ã  le faire.</li></ul><p>Il convient de remarquer que peut Ãªtre assimilÃ© au proxÃ©nÃ©tisme le fait, par quiconque, de quelque maniÃ¨re que ce soit, de faire office dâintermÃ©diaire entre deux personnes dont lâune se livre Ã  la prostitution et lâautre exploite ou rÃ©munÃ¨re la prostitution dâautrui.</p><h5>7. ATTEINTE AUX SYSTEMES DE TRAITEMENT AUTOMATISE DE DONNEES</h5><p>Sont visÃ©s notamment :</p><ul><li>le fait dâaccÃ©der ou de se maintenir frauduleusement dans tout ou partie dâun systÃ¨me de traitement automatisÃ© de donnÃ©es ;</li><li>le fait dâentraver ou de fausser le fonctionnement dâun tel systÃ¨me ;</li><li>le fait dâintroduire frauduleusement des donnÃ©es dans un tel systÃ¨me ou de supprimer ou de modifier frauduleusement les donnÃ©es quâil contient.</li></ul><h5>8. PUBLICITES MENSONGERES - PROTECTION DES CONSOMMATEURS</h5><p>Le Fournisseur dâun site Web doit veiller Ã  ce que les messages quâil diffuse ne comportent pas dâÃ©lÃ©ments faux (publicitÃ© mensongÃ¨re) ou de nature Ã  induire en erreur (publicitÃ© trompeuse).</p><p>Pour toute offre de vente dâun bien ou de fourniture de prestation de services qui est faite Ã  distance Ã  un consommateur, le professionnel indiquera le nom de son entreprise, ses coordonnÃ©es tÃ©lÃ©phoniques ainsi que lâadresse de son siÃ¨ge et, si elle est diffÃ©rente, celle de lâÃ©tablissement responsable de lâoffre, ainsi que le nom de la personne considÃ©rÃ©e comme le Directeur de publication.</p><h5>9. DISPOSITIONS LEGALES RELATIVES AUX SUBSTANCES STUPEFIANTES</h5><p>Peuvent Ãªtre passible dâemprisonnement et dâamende selon les lÃ©gislations locales :</p><ul><li>La provocation Ã  lâusage illicite de stupÃ©fiants ou au trafic de stupÃ©fiants, alors mÃªme que cette provocation nâa pas Ã©tÃ© suivie dâeffet, ou le fait de prÃ©senter ces infractions sous un jour favorable ;</li><li>La provocation, mÃªme non suivie dâeffet, Ã  lâusage de substances prÃ©sentÃ©es comme ayant les effets de substances ou plantes classÃ©es comme stupÃ©fiants.</li><li>Le transport, la dÃ©tention, lâoffre, la cession, lâacquisition ou lâemploi illicites de stupÃ©fiants</li><li>Le fait de faciliter, par quelque moyen que ce soit, lâusage illicite de stupÃ©fiants, de se faire dÃ©livrer des stupÃ©fiants au moyen dâordonnances fictives ou de complaisance, ou de dÃ©livrer des stupÃ©fiants sur la prÃ©sentation de telles ordonnances en connaissant leur caractÃ¨re fictif ou complaisant ;</li><li>La provocation dâun mineur Ã  lâusage de stupÃ©fiants ;</li><li>La provocation dâun mineur Ã  un trafic de stupÃ©fiants ;</li><li>La production ou la fabrication illicite de stupÃ©fiants ;</li><li>Lâimportation ou lâexportation illicite de stupÃ©fiants.</li></ul><h5>10. INFORMATIONS</h5><h6>10.1 Authentification des informations</h6><p>La source de lâinformation doit Ãªtre indiquÃ©e clairement et sâil sâagit dâun commentaire lâauteur devra Ãªtre nommÃ©ment dÃ©signÃ©.</p><h6>10.2.Fausses informations</h6><p>Le fait de communiquer ou de divulguer une fausse information dans le but de faire croire quâune destruction, une dÃ©gradation ou une dÃ©gradation dangereuse pour les personnes va Ãªtre ou a Ã©tÃ© commise ou de communiquer ou de divulguer une fausse information faisant croire Ã  un sinistre et de nature Ã  provoquer lâintervention inutile des secours est punissable.</p><h5>11. DISCRIMINATION</h5><p>Constitue une discrimination, toute distinction opÃ©rÃ©e entre les personnes physiques Ã  raison de leur origine, de leur sexe, de leur situation de famille, de leur Ã©tat de santÃ©, de leur handicap, de leurs mÅurs, de leurs opinions politiques, de leurs activitÃ©s syndicales, de leur appartenance ou de leur non-appartenance, vraie ou supposÃ©e, Ã  une ethnie, une nation, une race ou une religion dÃ©terminÃ©e.</p><p>Constitue Ã©galement une discrimination toute distinction opÃ©rÃ©e entre les personnes morales Ã  raison de lâorigine, du sexe, de la situation de famille, de lâÃ©tat de santÃ©, du handicap, des mÅurs, des opinions politiques, des activitÃ©s syndicales, de lâappartenance ou de la non appartenance, vraie ou supposÃ©e, Ã  une ethnie, une nation, une race ou une religion dÃ©terminÃ©e des membres ou de certains membres de ces personnes morales.</p><p>La discrimination Ã  lâÃ©gard dâune personne physique ou morale est punissable lorsquâelle consiste notamment Ã  refuser la fourniture dâun bien ou dâun service, Ã  subordonner la fourniture dâun bien ou dâun service Ã  une condition fondÃ©e sur lâun des Ã©lÃ©ments visÃ©s prÃ©cÃ©demment.</p><h5>12. ATTEINTE A LA REPRESENTATION DE LA PERSONNE</h5><p>Le fait de publier, par quelque voie que ce soit, le montage rÃ©alisÃ© avec les paroles ou lâimage dâune personne sans son consentement, sâil nâapparaÃ®t pas Ã  lâÃ©vidence quâil sâagit dâun montage ou sâil nâen est pas fait expressÃ©ment mention est punissable.</p><h5>13. PROTECTION DE LA PERSONNE</h5><p>Le fait de porter au moyen dâun procÃ©dÃ© quelconque volontairement atteinte Ã  la vie privÃ©e dâautrui est visÃ©.</p><h5>14. PROPRIETE INTELLECTUELLE ET CONCURRENCE DELOYALE</h5><p>Le Code de la PropriÃ©tÃ© Intellectuelle prohibe toute reprise dâÅuvre de lâesprit sans le consentement de lâauteur. De mÃªme, toute utilisation illicite de marque est constitutive de contrefaÃ§on, y compris dans les metatags des sites Internet.</p><p>En outre, les logiciels et la technologie sous-jacente attachÃ©s aux sites sont protÃ©gÃ©s et ne peuvent Ãªtre repris quâavec le consentement exprÃ¨s du titulaire des droits.</p><p>IndÃ©pendamment des actes susceptibles de constituer une contrefaÃ§on, toute reprise de droits appartenant Ã  autrui pourra Ãªtre poursuivie au titre de la concurrence dÃ©loyale et des agissements parasitaires, et entraÃ®ner la mise en cause de la responsabilitÃ© du contrevenant.</p><p>En particulier, avant dâinsÃ©rer un lien profond dirigÃ© vers un site tiers, il est conseillÃ© de vÃ©rifier si un tel lien est licite, ou de solliciter lâautorisation du site cible, afin de prÃ©venir tout acte qui pourrait a posteriori se rÃ©vÃ©ler constitutif de concurrence dÃ©loyale.</p><h5>15. DONNEES A CARACTERE PERSONNEL</h5><p>Toute personne physique ou morale se livrant Ã  la collecte de donnÃ©es Ã  caractÃ¨re personnel, Ã  titre gracieux ou onÃ©reux, est tenue de procÃ©der Ã  une dÃ©claration ad hoc du traitement dâautomatisation du procÃ©dÃ© de la collecte de ces donnÃ©es.</p><p>A titre dâexemple, est considÃ©rÃ©e comme une donnÃ©e Ã  caractÃ¨re personnel une simple adresse de courrier Ã©lectronique dont la collecte devrait en consÃ©quence Ãªtre dÃ©clarÃ©e.</p><p>Il sâagira Ã©galement dâinformer les personnes dont les donnÃ©es sont collectÃ©es de la finalitÃ© des traitements mis en Åuvre, de rectification et, le cas Ã©chÃ©ant, dâopposition aux donnÃ©es qui les concernent.</p><h5>16. DONNEES DE SANTE A CARACTERE PERSONNEL</h5><p>Les personnes exerÃ§ant lâactivitÃ© dâhÃ©bergement de donnÃ©es de santÃ© Ã  caractÃ¨re personnel devront disposer dâun agrÃ©ment conforme aux prescriptions lÃ©gales.</p><p>2Pit rappelle Ã  lâUtilisateur quâil lui appartient de se rÃ©fÃ©rer Ã  la liste des hÃ©bergeurs agrÃ©Ã©s pour tout hÃ©bergement de donnÃ©es de santÃ© Ã  caractÃ¨re personnel.</p>"\n    }]\n}', 'OK', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{"time":"2017-05-08 22:01:46","n_fn":"admin, admin","type":"document","format":"application\\/json","direction":"input","reference":"generic","content":"{\\n    \\"action\\": \\"add\\",\\n    \\"locale_1\\": \\"fr-FR\\",\\n    \\"type\\": \\"text\\\\\\/html\\",\\n    \\"path\\": \\"\\\\\\/root\\\\\\/public\\\\\\/resources\\\\\\/\\",\\n    \\"name\\": \\"deontology_chart\\",\\n    \\"summary\\": \\"<h4 style=\\\\\\"text-align: left;\\\\\\">Why having choosen this project ?<\\\\\\/h4><blockquote>Why P-PIT ? As a mean to contribute to deliver the promise of technology. Since 30 years, I have been following the main IT evolutions: The desktop, the enterprise applications, the Internet thriving, the smartphone. Huge progresses in fact, but at the same time a more and more complex accumulation of solution parcels without a real consistency as a whole.<\\\\\\/blockquote>\\",\\n    \\"summary_locale_1\\": \\"<h4 style=\\\\\\"text-align: left;\\\\\\">Pourquoi avoir entrepris ce projet ?<\\\\\\/h4><blockquote>Pourquoi P-PIT ? Pour contribuer \\\\u00e0 d\\\\u00e9livrer enfin la promesse du progr\\\\u00e8s technologique. Depuis 30 ans, j\\\\u2019ai suivi les grandes \\\\u00e9volutions de l\\\\u2019informatique : Le poste de travail, les applications d\\\\u2019entreprise, l\\\\u2019essor de l\\\\u2019internet, le smartphone. Des progr\\\\u00e8s consid\\\\u00e9rables certes, mais en parall\\\\u00e8le un empilement de plus en plus complexe d\\\\u2019\\\\u00eelots de solutions sans v\\\\u00e9ritable coh\\\\u00e9rence d\\\\u2019ensemble.<\\\\\\/blockquote>\\",\\n    \\"properties\\": {\\n        \\"title\\": \\"Deontology chart\\",\\n        \\"description\\": \\"\\",\\n        \\"date\\": \\"2017-05-07\\"\\n    },\\n    \\"properties_locale_1\\": {\\n        \\"title\\": \\"Charte d\\u00c3\\u00a9ontologique\\",\\n        \\"description\\": \\"\\",\\n        \\"date\\": \\"2017-05-07\\"\\n    },\\n    \\"parts\\": [{\\n        \\"content\\": \\"<div style=\\\\\\"font-size: 85%\\\\\\"><h4 style=\\\\\\"color: darkmagenta\\\\\\">CHARTE DEONTOLOGIQUE Version en date du 01\\/09\\/2016<\\/h4><h5>1. PREAMBULE<\\\\\\/h5><p>This Chart aims at recalling to the User of the 2Pit free solution the main principles of international law applicable to the Internet, associated with a a short comment as an illustration. Though the attention given to the redaction of this appendix, The 2Pit community cannot assume whatever responsability about possibly lacking informations, the present chart being by no means to be considered as presenting any exhaustivity. Furthermore, it is up to the User to refer to the whole legal frame being relevant to his context.<\\/p><p>So the 2Pit community strongly advises the User to ask for a consulting in order to address his specific problem. The User is responsible of the comments and content standing in his own site.<\\/p><p>It is clarified, first, that the User manages at his own matters of any legal, regulatory or administrative authorizations necessary to the setting or running of the Internet site.<\\/p><p>Secondly, the user commit t respect in the frame of the running of the site, the legal and deontological rules governing the exercice of its prodession, and more generally the expected use of ths Internet site.<\\/p><p>In any event, the User is responsible of the respect of common decency and public order, of the respect of lawds and regulating, especially regarding child protection and espect of human being. He commit in the same conditions to respect of the rules concerning personal data protection and more generally to the rules concerning third-party rights, regarding in particular intellectual property rights, and rights relative to information and web sites content.<\\/p><h5>2. COMMUNICATION SERVICES FOR THE ONLINE PUBLIC<\\/h5><p>A distinction is made between different people able to act on a web site<\\/p><h6>2.1 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 The Internet access provider<\\/h6><p>He is defined as the person whose activity is to offer an access to communication services for the online public.<\\/p><p>He is responsible to inform his subscribers on the existence of technical means allowing to restrict the access to or select certain services and to propose them at least one of these means.<\\/p><p>He is also responsible to infom them on the existence of means to securize their network.<\\/p><h6>2.2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 The host<\\/h6><p>He is defined as the physic or moral person who ensure, even for free, as to provide the public by the mean of the communication services for the online public, the storage of signals, documents, images, sounds and messages of any nature supplied by offerees of these services.<\\/p><p>The host should not be mistaken for the service provider who, as the case may be, let for the benefit of the host a dedicated service, such a service provider just providing a technical infrastructure.<\\/p><h6>2.3 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 The publisher of a communication service for the online public.<\\/h6><p>The publisher of the site will provide the public, in an open standard, with:<\\/p><ul><li>in the case of a public person: his last name, first name, place of residence ans phone number, along with if necessary the registration number on legal files,<\\/li><li>in the case of a moral person: his denomination, his head office, phone numbers, registration number in legal files, share capital, name of the director of publication, the name, address and phone number of his host.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>The publisher will also take care to display:<\\/p><ul><li>the applicable fare as the case may be,<\\/li><li>the advertising character of the webcasted messages.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>However, in the case of a sited published as non-professional, the publisher, in order to preserve his anonymity, is allowed to just provide the public, with only the name and address of his host, while taking care of beforehand insure he has communicated to the last, his personal identification informations.<\\/p><p>The constatation of an illicit content should give rise to a request formulated directly to the site publisher. In case of absence of the last, and since the content present an obviously illicit character, a dated notification can be addressed to the host with mention of the name and address of the addressee, the description of the litigious facts and their precise localization, the motivation for having the content retired, including the mention of legal dispositions and fact justifications, along with the copy of the correspondence addressed to the author or publisher of the litigious content, asking for its removal, its modification or, failing this, the justification of the author or publisher not being possibly reachable.<\\/p><p>The host has, in this respect, no general obligation of supervision of the contents he hosts.<\\/p><p>Finally, there exists rules which apply to all the service providers as information medium which are related, for the most, to the public order protection and the public decency respect.<\\/p><h5>3. PUBLIC ORDER<\\/h5><p>Nobody can depart from laws relative to public order.<\\/p><p>The confusion in public order is an evident breach of the public peace.<\\/p><h5>4. Public decency and youth<\\/h5><p>Nobody can depart from laws relative to public decency.<\\/p><p>Affront to public decency is defined by the fact either to make, transport, spread by whatever mean and with whatever support a message with a violent or pornographic character or with a nature which could seriously strike a blow at human dignity or encourage minor people to give oneself up to games physically putting them in danger, either to make business of such a message.<\\/p><h5>5. INCENTIVE TO SUICIDE<\\/h5><p>Are especially targeted:<\\/p><ul><li>the fact of provoke suicide, while the provocation has been followed by a suicide or a suicide attempt. As such, one could considere the Internet as a vector of provocation;<\\/li><li>the propaganda or advertising, whatever the mean, in favor of products, objects or methods advocated as means to give oneself death;<\\/li><li>the fact, by the mean of whatever process, to voluntarily strike a blow at others private life\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s intimity.<\\/li><\\/ul><h5>6. PROCURING<\\/h5><p>Is targeted the fact by anyone, whatever the mean:<\\/p><ul><li>To help, assist or protect others prostitution;<\\/li><li>To benefit from others prostitution, to share the products of it or to receive the subsidies from a person regularily engaged to prostitution;<\\/li><li>To hire, train, or divert a person towards prostitution or to pu pressure on her in order to prostitute or go on prostituting.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>It is worth remarking that can be assimilated to procuring the fact, by whoever, whith whatever mean, to act as an intermediary between two persons, one of whom is engaged to prostitution, and the other exploits or remunerates others prostitution.<\\/p><h5>7. BREACH TO AUTOMATED DATA PROCESSING SYSTEMS<\\/h5><p>Are specifically targeted:<\\/p><ul><li>the fact of accessing or staying fraudulently inside the whole or a part of an automated data processing system;<\\/li><li>the fact of hindering or skewing the functioning of such a system;<\\/li><li>the fact of introducing fraudulently data in such a system or suppressing or or fradulently modifying the contained data.<\\/li><\\/ul><h5>8. MISLEADING ADVERTISING - CONSUMER PROTECTION<\\/h5><p>The provider of a web site should make sure that the messages being webcasted do not consist of false elements or likely to lead one abstray.<\\/p><p>For any distance sale offer for a good or a service which is made to a consumer, the professional will mention the name of his enterprise, his phone number, the address of his head office and, if different, the one of theplace responsible of the offer, along with the name of the person considered as the publication responsible.<\\/p><h5>9. LEGAL DISPOSITIONS RELATIVE TO NARCOTIC SUBSTANCES<\\/h5><p>According to local laws, can be liable to imprisonment and fines:<\\/p><ul><li>The provocation to illicit use of stupefiants or to stupefiant traffic, even if that provocation has no been followed by any effect, or the fact to present favorably these offences;<\\/li><li>The provocation, even if not followed by effects, to the use of substances presented as having the effects of substances or plants that are classed as stupefiants;<\\/li><li>The transportation, detention, offer, transfer, purchase or illicit use of stupefiants;<\\/li><li>the fact of facilitating, by whatever mean, the illicit use of stupefiants, of obtaining stupefiants by the mean of fictifious prescription, or of delivering stupefiants based on the presentation of such prescriptions, while knowing the fictifious character;<\\/li><li>the provocation of a minor person to using stupefiants;<\\/li><li>the provocation of a minor person to the stupefiant traffic;<\\/li><li>the illicit production or making of stupefiants;<\\/li><li>the illicit import or export of stupefiants.<\\/li><\\/ul><h5>10. INFORMATIONS<\\/h5><h6>10.1 Informations authentication<\\/h6><p>The information origin should be clearly mentioned, and concerning a comment, the author should be designed by name.<\\/p><h6>10.2.False informations<\\/h6><p>The fact of communicating or leaking a false information in order to persuade that a destruction, a degradation or a dangerous degradation for persons is about to be, or has been committed, ot of communicating or leaking a false information in order to persuade about a disaster, and to cause the unnecessary intervention of first aid is punishable.<\\/p><h5>11. DISCRIMINATION<\\/h5><p>Constitute a discrimination, any distinction made between physical persons for the reason of their origin, sex, family situation, state of wealth, handicap, manners, political opinions, union activity, belonging or non-belonging, real or supposed, to an ethnic group, a nation, a race or a particular religion.<\\/p><p>Also constitue a discrimination any distinction made between moral persons for the reason of the origin, sex, family situation, state of wealth, handicap, manners, political opinions, union activity, belonging or non-belonging, real or supposed, to an ethnic group, a nation, a race or a particular religion of members or some of te members of these moral persons.<\\/p><p>The discrimination towards a physical or a moral person is punishable each time it consists in particular to refuse the providing of a good or service at a condition founded on one of the elements targeted before.<\\/p><h5>12. INFRINGEMENT TO THE PERSON REPRESENTATION<\\/h5><p>The fact of publishing, by whatever medium, the editing realized with the speech or the image of a person without his or her consent, each time it does not appears clearly that it is an editing, or if it is not expressly mentioned is punishable..<\\/p><h5>13. PROTECTION OF THE PERSON<\\/h5><p>The fact of volontarily undermining, by whatever process, to someone privacy is punishable.<\\/p><h5>14. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY AND UNFAIR COMPETITION<\\/h5><p>The intellectual property regulation prohibit any reuse of a work of the mind without the author consent. Likewise, any illicit use of marks constitutes an infringement, including in the metatags of Internet sites.<\\/p><p>Furthermore, software and the underlying technology linked to sites are protected and can only be reused with the express consent of the holder of the rights.<\\/p><p>Independently of the acts subject to constitute an counterfeit, ny reuse of rights belonging to others could be sued as regards to unfair competition, and lead to the implication of the offender\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s responsability.<\\/p><p>In particular, before inserting a deep link towards a third-party site, it is recommanded to verify is such a link is licit, or to ask the authorization of the target site, in order to prevent from any act which could reveal a posteriori as constituting an unfair competition.<\\/p><h5>15. PERSONAL DATA<\\/h5><p>Any physic or moral person engaged in the collect of personal data, freely or for a fee, is bound to proceed to an ad hoc declaration of the process of automation of the collect of these data.<\\/p><p>For example, is considered as being a personal data a simple email address which collect should consequently be declared.<\\/p><p>It will also be necessary to inform the persons whose data are collected about the finality of the implemented processes, about the possibility of rectification and, if necessary, of opposition to the data that concerns them.<\\/p><h5>16. HEALTH PERSONAL DATA<\\/h5><p>The persons who practise the activity of hosting health personal data should own an agreement conforming to legal prescriptions.<\\/p><p>2Pit recalls to the user that it is his\\/her responsability to refer to the list of authorized hosts for any health personal data hosting.<\\/p>\\",\\n        \\"content_locale_1\\": \\"<div style=\\\\\\"font-size: 85%\\\\\\"><h4 style=\\\\\\"color: darkmagenta\\\\\\">CHARTE DEONTOLOGIQUE Version en date du 01\\/09\\/2016<\\/h4><h5>1. PREAMBULE<\\/h5><p>La pr\\u00c3\\u00a9sente Charte a pour objet de rappeler \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Utilisateur de la solution libre 2Pit les principales r\\u00c3\\u00a8gles de droit international applicables \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Internet, associ\\u00c3\\u00a9s \\u00c3\\u00a0 un court commentaire \\u00c3\\u00a0 titre d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099illustration. Malgr\\u00c3\\u00a9 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099attention port\\u00c3\\u00a9e \\u00c3\\u00a0 la r\\u00c3\\u00a9daction de cette annexe, la communaut\\u00c3\\u00a9 2Pit ne peut assumer une quelconque responsabilit\\u00c3\\u00a9 du fait des informations qui n\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099y sont pas contenues, la pr\\u00c3\\u00a9sente charte ne pouvant en aucun cas \\u00c3\\u00aatre consid\\u00c3\\u00a9r\\u00c3\\u00a9e comme pr\\u00c3\\u00a9sentant un caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re exhaustif. Par ailleurs, il appartient \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Utilisateur de se reporter \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ensemble du cadre l\\u00c3\\u00a9gal le concernant.<\\/p><p>La communaut\\u00c3\\u00a9 2Pit conseille donc fortement \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Utilisateur de s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099adresser \\u00c3\\u00a0 un conseil pour traiter de son probl\\u00c3\\u00a8me particulier. L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099utilisateur est responsable des propos et des contenus figurant sur son propre site.<\\/p><p>Il est pr\\u00c3\\u00a9cis\\u00c3\\u00a9, en premier lieu, que l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Utilisateur fait son affaire personnelle de toutes les autorisations l\\u00c3\\u00a9gales, r\\u00c3\\u00a9glementaires ou administratives n\\u00c3\\u00a9cessaires \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ouverture et \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099exploitation du site Internet.<\\/p><p>En second lieu, l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099utilisateur s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099engage \\u00c3\\u00a0 respecter dans le cadre de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099exploitation du site, les r\\u00c3\\u00a8gles l\\u00c3\\u00a9gales et d\\u00c3\\u00a9ontologiques pouvant r\\u00c3\\u00a9gir l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099exercice de sa profession, et plus g\\u00c3\\u00a9n\\u00c3\\u00a9ralement l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099utilisation qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il envisage du site Internet.<\\/p><p>En tout \\u00c3\\u00a9tat de cause, l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Utilisateur est responsable du respect des bonnes m\\u00c5\\u0093urs et de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ordre public, du respect des Lois et R\\u00c3\\u00a8glements, notamment en mati\\u00c3\\u00a8re de protection des mineurs et du respect de la personne humaine. Il s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099engage dans les m\\u00c3\\u00aames conditions au respect des r\\u00c3\\u00a8gles relatives \\u00c3\\u00a0 la protection des donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es \\u00c3\\u00a0 caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re personnel et plus g\\u00c3\\u00a9n\\u00c3\\u00a9ralement de celles relatives aux droits des tiers, en particulier concernant les droits de propri\\u00c3\\u00a9t\\u00c3\\u00a9 intellectuelle, ainsi que les droits relatifs \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099information et au contenu des sites web.<\\/p><h5>2. SERVICES DE COMMUNICATION AU PUBLIC EN LIGNE<\\/h5><p>Une distinction est faite entre les diff\\u00c3\\u00a9rentes personnes susceptibles d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099intervenir sur un site Internet<\\/p><h6>2.1 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Le fournisseur d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099acc\\u00c3\\u00a8s \\u00c3\\u00a0 Internet<\\/h6><p>Il est d\\u00c3\\u00a9fini comme la personne dont l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099activit\\u00c3\\u00a9 est d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099offrir un acc\\u00c3\\u00a8s \\u00c3\\u00a0 des services de communication au public en ligne.<\\/p><p>Il lui appartient d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099informer ses abonn\\u00c3\\u00a9s de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099existence de moyens techniques permettant de restreindre l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099acc\\u00c3\\u00a8s \\u00c3\\u00a0 certains services ou de les s\\u00c3\\u00a9lectionner et de leur proposer au moins un de ces moyens.<\\/p><p>Il lui appartient \\u00c3\\u00a9galement de les informer de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099existence de moyens de s\\u00c3\\u00a9curisation de leur r\\u00c3\\u00a9seau.<\\/p><h6>2.2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergeur<\\/h6><p>Il est d\\u00c3\\u00a9fini comme la personne physique ou morale qui assure, m\\u00c3\\u00aame \\u00c3\\u00a0 titre gratuit, pour mise \\u00c3\\u00a0 disposition du public par les services de communication au public en ligne, le stockage de signaux, d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9crits, d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099images, de sons ou de messages de toute nature fournis par des destinataires de ces services.<\\/p><p>L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergeur ne doit pas \\u00c3\\u00aatre confondu avec le prestataire qui, le cas \\u00c3\\u00a9ch\\u00c3\\u00a9ant, loue au profit de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergeur un serveur d\\u00c3\\u00a9di\\u00c3\\u00a9, un tel prestataire se contentant de mettre \\u00c3\\u00a0 disposition une infrastructure technique.<\\/p><h6>2.3 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9diteur d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un service de communication au public en ligne.<\\/h6><p>L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9diteur du site mettra \\u00c3\\u00a0 disposition du public, dans un standard ouvert :<\\/p><ul><li>s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099agit d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099une personne physique : ses nom, pr\\u00c3\\u00a9nom, domicile et num\\u00c3\\u00a9ros de t\\u00c3\\u00a9l\\u00c3\\u00a9phone, ainsi que le cas \\u00c3\\u00a9ch\\u00c3\\u00a9ant le num\\u00c3\\u00a9ro de son inscription dans les registres l\\u00c3\\u00a9gaux,<\\/li><li>s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099agit d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099une personne morale : sa d\\u00c3\\u00a9nomination, son si\\u00c3\\u00a8ge social, num\\u00c3\\u00a9ros de t\\u00c3\\u00a9l\\u00c3\\u00a9phone, num\\u00c3\\u00a9ro de son inscription dans les registres l\\u00c3\\u00a9gaux, capital social, le nom du directeur de la publication, le nom, l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099adresse et les num\\u00c3\\u00a9ros de t\\u00c3\\u00a9l\\u00c3\\u00a9phone de son h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergeur.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9diteur veillera \\u00c3\\u00a9galement \\u00c3\\u00a0 afficher :<\\/p><ul><li>le tarif applicable le cas \\u00c3\\u00a9ch\\u00c3\\u00a9ant,<\\/li><li>le caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re publicitaire des messages diffus\\u00c3\\u00a9s.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>Toutefois, lorsque le site est \\u00c3\\u00a9dit\\u00c3\\u00a9 \\u00c3\\u00a0 titre non professionnel, l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9diteur, afin de pr\\u00c3\\u00a9server son anonymat, peut se contenter de tenir \\u00c3\\u00a0 la disposition du public, uniquement le nom et l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099adresse de son h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergeur, en ayant pris le soin de s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099assurer qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il a pr\\u00c3\\u00a9alablement communiqu\\u00c3\\u00a9 \\u00c3\\u00a0 ce dernier, ses \\u00c3\\u00a9l\\u00c3\\u00a9ments d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099identification personnelle.<\\/p><p>La constatation d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un contenu illicite doit donner lieu \\u00c3\\u00a0 une demande formul\\u00c3\\u00a9e directement aupr\\u00c3\\u00a8s de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9diteur du site. En cas de carence de ce dernier, et d\\u00c3\\u00a8s lors que le contenu pr\\u00c3\\u00a9sente un caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re manifestement illicite, une notification dat\\u00c3\\u00a9e pourra \\u00c3\\u00aatre adress\\u00c3\\u00a9e \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergeur en indiquant les coordonn\\u00c3\\u00a9es du notifiant, les nom et adresse du destinataire, la description des faits litigieux et leur localisation pr\\u00c3\\u00a9cise, les motifs pour lesquels le contenu doit \\u00c3\\u00aatre retir\\u00c3\\u00a9, comprenant la mention des dispositions l\\u00c3\\u00a9gales et des justifications de fait, ainsi que la copie de la correspondance adress\\u00c3\\u00a9e \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099auteur ou \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9diteur du contenu litigieux, demandant son retrait, sa modification ou, \\u00c3\\u00a0 d\\u00c3\\u00a9faut, la justification de ce que l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099auteur ou l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9diteur n\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099a pu \\u00c3\\u00aatre contact\\u00c3\\u00a9.<\\/p><p>L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergeur n\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099a, \\u00c3\\u00a0 cet \\u00c3\\u00a9gard, aucune obligation g\\u00c3\\u00a9n\\u00c3\\u00a9rale de surveillance des contenus qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il h\\u00c3\\u00a9berge.<\\/p><p>Enfin, il existe des r\\u00c3\\u00a8gles qui s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099appliquent \\u00c3\\u00a0 tous les fournisseurs de service en tant que supports d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099information et qui ont trait, pour la plupart, \\u00c3\\u00a0 la protection de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ordre public et au respect des bonnes m\\u00c5\\u0093urs.<\\/p><h5>3. ORDRE PUBLIC<\\/h5><p>Nul ne peut d\\u00c3\\u00a9roger aux lois qui int\\u00c3\\u00a9ressent l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ordre public.<\\/p><p>Le trouble \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ordre public est une atteinte manifeste \\u00c3\\u00a0 la paix publique.<\\/p><h5>4. BONNES MOEURS ET JEUNESSE<\\/h5><p>Nul ne peut d\\u00c3\\u00a9roger aux lois qui int\\u00c3\\u00a9ressent les bonnes m\\u00c5\\u0093urs.<\\/p><p>L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099outrage aux bonnes m\\u00c5\\u0093urs est d\\u00c3\\u00a9fini par le fait soit de fabriquer, de transporter, de diffuser par quelque moyen que ce soit et quel qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099en soit le support un message \\u00c3\\u00a0 caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re violent ou pornographique ou de nature \\u00c3\\u00a0 porter gravement atteinte \\u00c3\\u00a0 la dignit\\u00c3\\u00a9 humaine ou \\u00c3\\u00a0 inciter des mineurs \\u00c3\\u00a0 se livrer \\u00c3\\u00a0 des jeux les mettant physiquement en danger, soit de faire commerce d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un tel message.<\\/p><h5>5. INCITATION AU SUICIDE<\\/h5><p>Sont vis\\u00c3\\u00a9s notamment :<\\/p><ul><li>Le fait de provoquer au suicide, lorsque la provocation a \\u00c3\\u00a9t\\u00c3\\u00a9 suivie d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un suicide ou d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099une tentative de suicide. A ce titre, on pourrait consid\\u00c3\\u00a9rer comme vecteur de provocation l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Internet ;<\\/li><li>La propagande ou la publicit\\u00c3\\u00a9, quel qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099en soit le mode, en faveur de produits, objets ou de m\\u00c3\\u00a9thodes pr\\u00c3\\u00a9conis\\u00c3\\u00a9s comme moyens de se donner la mort;<\\/li><li>Le fait, au moyen d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un proc\\u00c3\\u00a9d\\u00c3\\u00a9 quelconque, de porter volontairement atteinte \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099intimit\\u00c3\\u00a9 de la vie priv\\u00c3\\u00a9e d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099autrui.<\\/li><\\/ul><h5>6. PROXENETISME<\\/h5><p>Sont vis\\u00c3\\u00a9s le fait par quiconque, de quelque mani\\u00c3\\u00a8re que ce soit :<\\/p><ul><li>D\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099aider, d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099assister ou de prot\\u00c3\\u00a9ger la prostitution d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099autrui ;<\\/li><li>De tirer profit de la prostitution d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099autrui, d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099en partager les produits ou de recevoir les subsides d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099une personne se livrant habituellement \\u00c3\\u00a0 la prostitution ;<\\/li><li>D\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099embaucher, d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099entra\\u00c3\\u00aener ou de d\\u00c3\\u00a9tourner une personne en vue de la prostitution ou d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099exercer sur elle une pression pour qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099elle se prostitue ou continue \\u00c3\\u00a0 le faire.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>Il convient de remarquer que peut \\u00c3\\u00aatre assimil\\u00c3\\u00a9 au prox\\u00c3\\u00a9n\\u00c3\\u00a9tisme le fait, par quiconque, de quelque mani\\u00c3\\u00a8re que ce soit, de faire office d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099interm\\u00c3\\u00a9diaire entre deux personnes dont l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099une se livre \\u00c3\\u00a0 la prostitution et l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099autre exploite ou r\\u00c3\\u00a9mun\\u00c3\\u00a8re la prostitution d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099autrui.<\\/p><h5>7. ATTEINTE AUX SYSTEMES DE TRAITEMENT AUTOMATISE DE DONNEES<\\/h5><p>Sont vis\\u00c3\\u00a9s notamment :<\\/p><ul><li>le fait d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099acc\\u00c3\\u00a9der ou de se maintenir frauduleusement dans tout ou partie d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un syst\\u00c3\\u00a8me de traitement automatis\\u00c3\\u00a9 de donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es ;<\\/li><li>le fait d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099entraver ou de fausser le fonctionnement d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un tel syst\\u00c3\\u00a8me ;<\\/li><li>le fait d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099introduire frauduleusement des donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es dans un tel syst\\u00c3\\u00a8me ou de supprimer ou de modifier frauduleusement les donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il contient.<\\/li><\\/ul><h5>8. PUBLICITES MENSONGERES - PROTECTION DES CONSOMMATEURS<\\/h5><p>Le Fournisseur d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un site Web doit veiller \\u00c3\\u00a0 ce que les messages qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il diffuse ne comportent pas d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9l\\u00c3\\u00a9ments faux (publicit\\u00c3\\u00a9 mensong\\u00c3\\u00a8re) ou de nature \\u00c3\\u00a0 induire en erreur (publicit\\u00c3\\u00a9 trompeuse).<\\/p><p>Pour toute offre de vente d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un bien ou de fourniture de prestation de services qui est faite \\u00c3\\u00a0 distance \\u00c3\\u00a0 un consommateur, le professionnel indiquera le nom de son entreprise, ses coordonn\\u00c3\\u00a9es t\\u00c3\\u00a9l\\u00c3\\u00a9phoniques ainsi que l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099adresse de son si\\u00c3\\u00a8ge et, si elle est diff\\u00c3\\u00a9rente, celle de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9tablissement responsable de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099offre, ainsi que le nom de la personne consid\\u00c3\\u00a9r\\u00c3\\u00a9e comme le Directeur de publication.<\\/p><h5>9. DISPOSITIONS LEGALES RELATIVES AUX SUBSTANCES STUPEFIANTES<\\/h5><p>Peuvent \\u00c3\\u00aatre passible d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099emprisonnement et d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099amende selon les l\\u00c3\\u00a9gislations locales :<\\/p><ul><li>La provocation \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099usage illicite de stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants ou au trafic de stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants, alors m\\u00c3\\u00aame que cette provocation n\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099a pas \\u00c3\\u00a9t\\u00c3\\u00a9 suivie d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099effet, ou le fait de pr\\u00c3\\u00a9senter ces infractions sous un jour favorable ;<\\/li><li>La provocation, m\\u00c3\\u00aame non suivie d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099effet, \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099usage de substances pr\\u00c3\\u00a9sent\\u00c3\\u00a9es comme ayant les effets de substances ou plantes class\\u00c3\\u00a9es comme stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants.<\\/li><li>Le transport, la d\\u00c3\\u00a9tention, l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099offre, la cession, l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099acquisition ou l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099emploi illicites de stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants<\\/li><li>Le fait de faciliter, par quelque moyen que ce soit, l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099usage illicite de stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants, de se faire d\\u00c3\\u00a9livrer des stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants au moyen d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ordonnances fictives ou de complaisance, ou de d\\u00c3\\u00a9livrer des stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants sur la pr\\u00c3\\u00a9sentation de telles ordonnances en connaissant leur caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re fictif ou complaisant ;<\\/li><li>La provocation d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un mineur \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099usage de stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants ;<\\/li><li>La provocation d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un mineur \\u00c3\\u00a0 un trafic de stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants ;<\\/li><li>La production ou la fabrication illicite de stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants ;<\\/li><li>L\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099importation ou l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099exportation illicite de stup\\u00c3\\u00a9fiants.<\\/li><\\/ul><h5>10. INFORMATIONS<\\/h5><h6>10.1 Authentification des informations<\\/h6><p>La source de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099information doit \\u00c3\\u00aatre indiqu\\u00c3\\u00a9e clairement et s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099agit d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un commentaire l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099auteur devra \\u00c3\\u00aatre nomm\\u00c3\\u00a9ment d\\u00c3\\u00a9sign\\u00c3\\u00a9.<\\/p><h6>10.2.Fausses informations<\\/h6><p>Le fait de communiquer ou de divulguer une fausse information dans le but de faire croire qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099une destruction, une d\\u00c3\\u00a9gradation ou une d\\u00c3\\u00a9gradation dangereuse pour les personnes va \\u00c3\\u00aatre ou a \\u00c3\\u00a9t\\u00c3\\u00a9 commise ou de communiquer ou de divulguer une fausse information faisant croire \\u00c3\\u00a0 un sinistre et de nature \\u00c3\\u00a0 provoquer l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099intervention inutile des secours est punissable.<\\/p><h5>11. DISCRIMINATION<\\/h5><p>Constitue une discrimination, toute distinction op\\u00c3\\u00a9r\\u00c3\\u00a9e entre les personnes physiques \\u00c3\\u00a0 raison de leur origine, de leur sexe, de leur situation de famille, de leur \\u00c3\\u00a9tat de sant\\u00c3\\u00a9, de leur handicap, de leurs m\\u00c5\\u0093urs, de leurs opinions politiques, de leurs activit\\u00c3\\u00a9s syndicales, de leur appartenance ou de leur non-appartenance, vraie ou suppos\\u00c3\\u00a9e, \\u00c3\\u00a0 une ethnie, une nation, une race ou une religion d\\u00c3\\u00a9termin\\u00c3\\u00a9e.<\\/p><p>Constitue \\u00c3\\u00a9galement une discrimination toute distinction op\\u00c3\\u00a9r\\u00c3\\u00a9e entre les personnes morales \\u00c3\\u00a0 raison de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099origine, du sexe, de la situation de famille, de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9tat de sant\\u00c3\\u00a9, du handicap, des m\\u00c5\\u0093urs, des opinions politiques, des activit\\u00c3\\u00a9s syndicales, de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099appartenance ou de la non appartenance, vraie ou suppos\\u00c3\\u00a9e, \\u00c3\\u00a0 une ethnie, une nation, une race ou une religion d\\u00c3\\u00a9termin\\u00c3\\u00a9e des membres ou de certains membres de ces personnes morales.<\\/p><p>La discrimination \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9gard d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099une personne physique ou morale est punissable lorsqu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099elle consiste notamment \\u00c3\\u00a0 refuser la fourniture d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un bien ou d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un service, \\u00c3\\u00a0 subordonner la fourniture d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un bien ou d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un service \\u00c3\\u00a0 une condition fond\\u00c3\\u00a9e sur l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un des \\u00c3\\u00a9l\\u00c3\\u00a9ments vis\\u00c3\\u00a9s pr\\u00c3\\u00a9c\\u00c3\\u00a9demment.<\\/p><h5>12. ATTEINTE A LA REPRESENTATION DE LA PERSONNE<\\/h5><p>Le fait de publier, par quelque voie que ce soit, le montage r\\u00c3\\u00a9alis\\u00c3\\u00a9 avec les paroles ou l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099image d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099une personne sans son consentement, s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il n\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099appara\\u00c3\\u00aet pas \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c3\\u00a9vidence qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099agit d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un montage ou s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il n\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099en est pas fait express\\u00c3\\u00a9ment mention est punissable.<\\/p><h5>13. PROTECTION DE LA PERSONNE<\\/h5><p>Le fait de porter au moyen d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un proc\\u00c3\\u00a9d\\u00c3\\u00a9 quelconque volontairement atteinte \\u00c3\\u00a0 la vie priv\\u00c3\\u00a9e d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099autrui est vis\\u00c3\\u00a9.<\\/p><h5>14. PROPRIETE INTELLECTUELLE ET CONCURRENCE DELOYALE<\\/h5><p>Le Code de la Propri\\u00c3\\u00a9t\\u00c3\\u00a9 Intellectuelle prohibe toute reprise d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00c5\\u0093uvre de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099esprit sans le consentement de l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099auteur. De m\\u00c3\\u00aame, toute utilisation illicite de marque est constitutive de contrefa\\u00c3\\u00a7on, y compris dans les metatags des sites Internet.<\\/p><p>En outre, les logiciels et la technologie sous-jacente attach\\u00c3\\u00a9s aux sites sont prot\\u00c3\\u00a9g\\u00c3\\u00a9s et ne peuvent \\u00c3\\u00aatre repris qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099avec le consentement expr\\u00c3\\u00a8s du titulaire des droits.<\\/p><p>Ind\\u00c3\\u00a9pendamment des actes susceptibles de constituer une contrefa\\u00c3\\u00a7on, toute reprise de droits appartenant \\u00c3\\u00a0 autrui pourra \\u00c3\\u00aatre poursuivie au titre de la concurrence d\\u00c3\\u00a9loyale et des agissements parasitaires, et entra\\u00c3\\u00aener la mise en cause de la responsabilit\\u00c3\\u00a9 du contrevenant.<\\/p><p>En particulier, avant d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ins\\u00c3\\u00a9rer un lien profond dirig\\u00c3\\u00a9 vers un site tiers, il est conseill\\u00c3\\u00a9 de v\\u00c3\\u00a9rifier si un tel lien est licite, ou de solliciter l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099autorisation du site cible, afin de pr\\u00c3\\u00a9venir tout acte qui pourrait a posteriori se r\\u00c3\\u00a9v\\u00c3\\u00a9ler constitutif de concurrence d\\u00c3\\u00a9loyale.<\\/p><h5>15. DONNEES A CARACTERE PERSONNEL<\\/h5><p>Toute personne physique ou morale se livrant \\u00c3\\u00a0 la collecte de donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es \\u00c3\\u00a0 caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re personnel, \\u00c3\\u00a0 titre gracieux ou on\\u00c3\\u00a9reux, est tenue de proc\\u00c3\\u00a9der \\u00c3\\u00a0 une d\\u00c3\\u00a9claration ad hoc du traitement d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099automatisation du proc\\u00c3\\u00a9d\\u00c3\\u00a9 de la collecte de ces donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es.<\\/p><p>A titre d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099exemple, est consid\\u00c3\\u00a9r\\u00c3\\u00a9e comme une donn\\u00c3\\u00a9e \\u00c3\\u00a0 caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re personnel une simple adresse de courrier \\u00c3\\u00a9lectronique dont la collecte devrait en cons\\u00c3\\u00a9quence \\u00c3\\u00aatre d\\u00c3\\u00a9clar\\u00c3\\u00a9e.<\\/p><p>Il s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099agira \\u00c3\\u00a9galement d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099informer les personnes dont les donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es sont collect\\u00c3\\u00a9es de la finalit\\u00c3\\u00a9 des traitements mis en \\u00c5\\u0093uvre, de rectification et, le cas \\u00c3\\u00a9ch\\u00c3\\u00a9ant, d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099opposition aux donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es qui les concernent.<\\/p><h5>16. DONNEES DE SANTE A CARACTERE PERSONNEL<\\/h5><p>Les personnes exer\\u00c3\\u00a7ant l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099activit\\u00c3\\u00a9 d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergement de donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es de sant\\u00c3\\u00a9 \\u00c3\\u00a0 caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re personnel devront disposer d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099un agr\\u00c3\\u00a9ment conforme aux prescriptions l\\u00c3\\u00a9gales.<\\/p><p>2Pit rappelle \\u00c3\\u00a0 l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Utilisateur qu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099il lui appartient de se r\\u00c3\\u00a9f\\u00c3\\u00a9rer \\u00c3\\u00a0 la liste des h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergeurs agr\\u00c3\\u00a9\\u00c3\\u00a9s pour tout h\\u00c3\\u00a9bergement de donn\\u00c3\\u00a9es de sant\\u00c3\\u00a9 \\u00c3\\u00a0 caract\\u00c3\\u00a8re personnel.<\\/p>\\"\\n    }]\\n}"},{"time":"2017-05-08 22:03:52","n_fn":"admin, admin","status":"processed","http_status":"Consistency"},{"time":"2017-05-08 22:06:27","n_fn":"admin, admin","http_status":"OK"}]', '2017-05-08 22:01:46', 1, '2017-05-08 22:06:27', 1);
